.TH "dev_uc_sync_multiple" 9 "dev_uc_sync_multiple" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dev_uc_sync_multiple \- Synchronize device's unicast list to another device, but allow for multiple calls to sync to multiple devices.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dev_uc_sync_multiple
.BI "(struct net_device *to "  ","
.BI "struct net_device *from "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "to" 12
destination device
.IP "from" 12
source device

Add newly added addresses to the destination device and release
addresses that have been deleted from the source. The source device
must be locked by netif_addr_lock_bh.

This function is intended to be called from the dev->set_rx_mode
function of layered software devices.  It allows for a single source
device to be synced to multiple destination devices.
